6 R

Raov()

# 
teaching_method <- factor(rep(c("A", "B", "C"), each = 10))
score <- c(85, 88, 90, 87, 86, 89, 91, 92, 84, 87,
           78, 82, 80, 79, 81, 83, 85, 84, 80, 81,
           92, 94, 93, 95, 91, 90, 96, 94, 93, 92)

# 
data <- data.frame(TeachingMethod = teaching_method, Score = score)

# 
anova_result <- aov(Score ~ TeachingMethod, data = data)

# 
summary(anova_result)
##                Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value   Pr(>F)    
## TeachingMethod  2  688.2   344.1   68.82 2.51e-11 ***
## Residuals      27  135.0     5.0                     
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
plot(anova_result)

  • Df

  • Sum Sq

  • Mean Sq

  • F value

  • Pr(>F)pp0.05

  • F value = 68.82F

  • p-value = 2.51e-11p0.0595%

Rggplot2

# ggplot2
library(ggplot2)

ggplot(data, aes(x = TeachingMethod, y = Score, fill = TeachingMethod)) +

  theme_minimal()

RTukeyHSD()

# Tukey
tukey_result <- TukeyHSD(anova_result)

# 
print(tukey_result)
